<p>we are currently have two neo’s with 100:1 gear ratios on each end pivoting our end effector. I am looking to convert the rotations of the neos to degrees.</p>
<p>this is currently how we are trying to do this, does this look correct?</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">    private double getDegrees() {
        return (pivotEncoder.getPosition() * 360) * 100;
    }
</code></pre>
<p>we are also using a toughbox mini with two neos and a 8.45:1 gear ratio, we are looking to convert the neo rotations to inches, this is currently how we are doing this,</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public static final double GEAR_RATIO = 8.45;
public static final double SPROCKET_PITCH_DIAMETER = 1.910;
public static final double ENCODER_CONVERSION_FACTOR = 2 * (GEAR_RATIO * (Math.PI * SPROCKET_PITCH_DIAMETER));
</code></pre>
